{"TopicId":173962,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion - A centered version for all rover wheels (yes, even that gigantic one that nobody uses)","CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T13:58:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T13:58:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be great if we could have a variant of all the rover wheels that are perfectly centered like landing gear. For all your motorcycle\u00A0needs!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-16T14:05:51Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2018 02:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Fireheart318\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T14:48:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like a fun idea, however to be useful there is a need for a few other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMotorcycles and Bikes stay stable when driving though the gyroscopic effect. This is not simulated in KSPs physics. Additionally the wheels are\u00A0infinitesimal thin (for the physics calculation)\u00A0making the bike even more unstable. This would have to be taken care of. Or simply use\u00A0reaction wheels en masse for that\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d also\u00A0need some control to lean the bikes to the sides when steering, otherwise you will most likely miss the turn\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-16T14:49:52Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2018 02:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T14:51:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeople already make motorcycles in game with the current wheels, I have myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReaction wheels take care of balance and leaning to turn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure there is an actual game-play need for motorcycle style rovers though? I certainly wouldn\u0027t complain about some expanded wheel options; but I don\u0027t think it\u0027s a huge priority.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T16:28:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523887128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159932\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fireheart318\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Fireheart318 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be great if we could have a variant of all the rover wheels that are perfectly centered like landing gear. For all your motorcycle\u00A0needs!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIF only to have caster-type wheels with 180-degree steering, and a steering range you can set.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T17:04:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m just chiming in in defense of the gigantic rover wheels. I use them for gigantic (well, medium sized imho) refueling rovers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fireheart318","CreatedById":159932,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T18:38:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355974\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523896128\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FleshJeb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, FleshJeb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIF only to have caster-type wheels with 180-degree steering, and a steering range you can set.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou mean for this kind of car? Please say yes!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022racer_x_speed_racer_movie_crash.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022223\u0022 src=\u0022https://i2.wp.com/speedrally.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/racer_x_speed_racer_movie_crash.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T19:22:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355906\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523890125\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like a fun idea, however to be useful there is a need for a few other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMotorcycles and Bikes stay stable when driving though the gyroscopic effect. This is not simulated in KSPs physics. Additionally the wheels are\u00A0infinitesimal thin (for the physics calculation)\u00A0making the bike even more unstable. This would have to be taken care of. Or simply use\u00A0reaction wheels en masse for that\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d also\u00A0need some control to lean the bikes to the sides when steering, otherwise you will most likely miss the turn\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair points (even considering that people already have workarounds for those issues)...however It seems that is more a request for something that \u003Cem\u003Elooks\u003C/em\u003E than something that \u003Cem\u003Eworks. \u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that could be used not only by Bikes but also Trikes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EnderKid2","CreatedById":145622,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-17T05:10:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe must have all of the types of wheels!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOmniwheels!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechanum wheels!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSwerve drive!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-23T06:37:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355906\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523890125\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 16/04/2018 at 10:48 AM, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027d also\u00A0need some control to lean the bikes to the sides when steering, otherwise you will most likely miss the turn\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/1zrHCIkgEtU?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RedPandaz","CreatedById":168757,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-10T13:51:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173962\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523898298\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022juanml82\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/16/2018 at 10:04 AM, juanml82 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m just chiming in in defense of the gigantic rover wheels. I use them for gigantic (well, medium sized imho) refueling rovers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re the \u003Cb\u003Eonly\u003Ci\u003E\u00A0\u003C/i\u003E\u003C/b\u003Eones I use \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn this topic, we do need tank treads. Maybe a way to create custom tank treads? [like placing down wheels for them and then clicking them in the order the tread passes over them?]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}